detaileddescription.para:
Enables a device-specific interrupt in the NVIC interrupt controller.
IRQn
External interrupt number. Value cannot be negative.

Disables a device-specific interrupt in the NVIC interrupt controller.
IRQn
External interrupt number. Value cannot be negative.

Reads the pending register in the NVIC and returns the pending bit for the specified interrupt.
IRQn
Interrupt number.
0 Interrupt status is not pending.
1 Interrupt status is pending.

Sets the pending bit of an external interrupt.
IRQn
Interrupt number. Value cannot be negative.

Clears the pending bit of an external interrupt.
IRQn
External interrupt number. Value cannot be negative.

Sets the priority of an interrupt.
The priority cannot be set for every core interrupt.
IRQn
Interrupt number.
priority
Priority to set.

Reads the priority of an interrupt. The interrupt number can be positive to specify an external (device specific) interrupt, or negative to specify an internal (core) interrupt.
IRQn
Interrupt number.
Interrupt Priority. Value is aligned automatically to the implemented priority bits of the microcontroller.
Initiates a system reset request to reset the MCU.

Initializes the System Timer and its interrupt, and starts the System Tick Timer. Counter is in free running mode to generate periodic interrupts.
ticks
Number of ticks between two interrupts.
0 Function succeeded.
1 Function failed.
When the variable __Vendor_SysTickConfig is set to 1, then the function SysTick_Config is not included. In this case, the file device.h must contain a vendor-specific implementation of this function.
